    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because the ASTM F1717 protocol is a fixed regulatory standard and parametric variation of test conditions is not feasible within the submission context. All three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (< 10% difference, E/uval < 1.96). Overall credibility is sufficient to support the Medium assurance level for this Class II device COU.",
